      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PEACHESNCREAM (8) had been showing ability the trials then brought that to the races when she kicked off her career by beating all of these rivals for a win by close to 6m at this circuit and distance. A wider draw poses more of a challenge but she looks talented and has upside. MAC TILLY (4) drew the outside barrier when resuming but was able to work to the front before boxing on for fourth behind PEACHESNCREAM. She'll be fitter for that and will enjoy a much better draw. SOPHIES WISH (10) did a good job to win at start number two at Bathurst two back before racing parked when third last start. Cops the outside barrier but can be competitive with even luck as can SWINGING QUEEN (7) who draws wider than when runner-up to PEACHESNCREAM last start but has yet to miss the top-four this time in. COCTEAU DIAMOND (1) is better served by the ace draw for her second start so has first four claims.",
